Favoured Model: Mixed effects ordinal regression (stacked data)

Fit model

Here are all key variables in model.

Note I’ve used a rolling average for “EU a good thing” for the years 2015:2017 that were in the spreadsheet.

# Fit model
m1 = clmm(europ2 ~ level * dim + net_bal_pc + goodMu + equi17 + selfrule + vis4 + words + year2 + sourceFormat + (1|country) +  (1|site),
          Hess = TRUE,
          data = df,
          threshold = "flexible")

Plot main regression results

We have somewhat cleaner results for the Europeanization question in terms of level and the interaction with Frame.

Beginning with the no interaction model it looks like No Europ_ is more unlikely at the national level; on the other hand High Europ_ is less likely at the regional level.

The interaction effect by Frames add some nuance to this. For Economic frames there is a big difference between Regional and National - much more likely to be No Europ_ at the regional level than national. There is also a difference on the medium Europ_ between the two for the Economics frame (more Europ_ for the national); and similarly for High Europ_.

Basically, the differences seem to be mostly driven by the Economics frame -Politics exhibit less difference.
